1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.kissasia.net Support Admin)

2
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,118
[rock music playing]

3
00:00:44,942 --> 00:00:46,694
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

4
00:00:46,777 --> 00:00:47,903
[exhales sharply]

5
00:00:48,737 --> 00:00:50,948
[chuckles]

6
00:00:52,074 --> 00:00:53,576
He's not gonna look for it.

7
00:00:53,659 --> 00:00:55,953
Math isn't going on the web novel website

8
00:00:56,036 --> 00:00:57,371
and searching

9
00:00:58,205 --> 00:01:00,082
for We Were Friends just to

10
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:01,667
check this.

11
00:01:03,210 --> 00:01:04,628
He never would.

12
00:01:04,712 --> 00:01:07,172
[inhales sharply, sighs]

13
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:09,717
[chuckles]

14
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:10,801
PAZER WEB NOVEL PORTAL

15
00:01:10,885 --> 00:01:12,136
WE WERE FRIENDS

16
00:01:12,219 --> 00:01:15,931
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

17
00:01:17,725 --> 00:01:19,143
…YOON ONLY HAD EYES FOR TAE-HA…

18
00:01:28,110 --> 00:01:29,361
[scoffs]

19
00:01:29,445 --> 00:01:31,780
This girl is something else.

20
00:01:34,283 --> 00:01:35,326
[sighs]

21
00:01:39,163 --> 00:01:40,414
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 1

22
00:01:44,335 --> 00:01:45,336
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 2

23
00:01:47,296 --> 00:01:48,380
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 3

24
00:01:50,466 --> 00:01:52,885
END OF EPISODE 3

25
00:02:01,477 --> 00:02:04,939
CHAPTER 23: YOUR ROUGH THOUGHTS
AND ANXIOUS LOOKS

26
00:02:05,022 --> 00:02:07,650
[Woo-su chewing] Mmm. Mmm.

27
00:02:10,235 --> 00:02:12,446
EPISODE 7

28
00:02:14,281 --> 00:02:21,121
So, it turns out that the EBC people
are very excited about the math class too.

29
00:02:21,205 --> 00:02:22,915
[Gi-jeon, Dong-ju chuckling]

30
00:02:22,998 --> 00:02:26,627
No wonder. I'd be excited too.
I mean, it's the elite math genius' class.

31
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:29,338
-[chuckles] Isn't that right? Right?
-Mm-hmm. Mmm.

32
00:02:30,339 --> 00:02:32,758
Of course, I respect your decision.

33
00:02:32,841 --> 00:02:34,051
You don't have to feel burdened at all.

34
00:02:34,134 --> 00:02:36,553
-Not at all.
-Mmm! That's right.

35
00:02:36,637 --> 00:02:39,890
But you're human,
and maybe you changed your mind, right?

36
00:02:39,974 --> 00:02:43,060
So, let me ask one last time,
did you perhaps change your mind…

37
00:02:43,143 --> 00:02:44,144
Uh, no?

38
00:02:46,355 --> 00:02:47,439
[door closes]

39
00:02:48,399 --> 00:02:49,942
-Do something.
-[Gi-jeon groans]

40
00:02:59,785 --> 00:03:00,869
[Young-hee] Today's the day.

41
00:03:00,953 --> 00:03:06,250
Therefore, I'm going to ask you
that until the filming is over

42
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:09,545
and until EBC production crew
leaves the school,

43
00:03:09,628 --> 00:03:11,088
please stay focused

44
00:03:11,171 --> 00:03:14,967
and refrain from saying anything
that may work against our school.

45
00:03:15,801 --> 00:03:19,763
And I will ask,
especially the homeroom teachers,

46
00:03:19,847 --> 00:03:22,141
to please make sure
you keep the students attire

47
00:03:22,224 --> 00:03:24,518
and behavior under control.

48
00:03:25,102 --> 00:03:29,523
That way, we will have successful
and smooth results!

49
00:03:29,606 --> 00:03:31,316
-[teacher 1] Yes, ma'am.
-[teacher 2] Yes, ma'am.

50
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:35,904
Good luck, especially to our new teachers,
and the hero of this event,

51
00:03:35,988 --> 00:03:37,364
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

52
00:03:38,157 --> 00:03:42,494
♪ Good luck, Mr. Ga Woo-su ♪

53
00:03:42,578 --> 00:03:44,371
-Yes.
-Please do a good job.

54
00:03:45,456 --> 00:03:48,459
You can do it!

55
00:03:49,585 --> 00:03:51,670
Mr. Da-ju, are you sure about this?

56
00:03:51,754 --> 00:03:55,090
Yes, all roads lead to Seoul.
Isn't that right, ma'am?

57
00:03:55,174 --> 00:03:57,426
Mmm. [chuckles]

58
00:03:57,509 --> 00:04:00,637
-Auntie, Auntie!
-[cheers]

59
00:04:00,721 --> 00:04:02,514
Here comes our main character.

60
00:04:02,598 --> 00:04:05,726
Wow, Mr. E-den.
Look at that outfit. [gasps]

61
00:04:05,809 --> 00:04:08,896
Wow. You are born for the spotlight, huh?

62
00:04:08,979 --> 00:04:11,356
-Mr. Da-ju, I can always rely on you.
-[chuckling]

63
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:13,317
-Yes.
-Good.

64
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,735
Mmm.

65
00:04:14,818 --> 00:04:17,613
So you're our dear principal's nephew.
[chuckles]

66
00:04:17,696 --> 00:04:20,032
-[chuckles]
-[scoffs]

67
00:04:20,824 --> 00:04:22,826
[door opens, closes]

68
00:04:22,910 --> 00:04:23,911
[scoffs]

69
00:04:24,745 --> 00:04:28,123
Auntie, you do know what the highlight
of this shoot is, right?

70
00:04:28,207 --> 00:04:29,750
It's my flute solo.

71
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,877
Up on stage, and the curtains open.

72
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:34,505
Then a spotlight hits me perfectly.

73
00:04:34,588 --> 00:04:37,049
Ha. Then that's it. It's game over.

74
00:04:37,132 --> 00:04:40,469
-Sure, but drink this first. [chuckles]
-Okay.

75
00:04:41,678 --> 00:04:43,222
-Huh.
-What?

76
00:04:43,847 --> 00:04:45,474
[stammers]

77
00:04:48,435 --> 00:04:52,064
-This is one of my favorite coffee shops.
-Yes, I know.

78
00:04:52,147 --> 00:04:54,233
Drink it up.

79
00:04:54,316 --> 00:04:56,068
Uh-huh. A little more. More.

80
00:04:57,486 --> 00:05:00,239
A little more. More. More.

81
00:05:03,408 --> 00:05:04,576
[winces]

82
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:07,121
[students chattering]

83
00:05:25,556 --> 00:05:27,266
-[imitates flute]
-I like that.

84
00:05:27,349 --> 00:05:29,935
What if I go on TV and become too popular
to be a teacher?

85
00:05:30,018 --> 00:05:32,312
-[laughs]
-[laughing] Oh, my god.

86
00:05:32,396 --> 00:05:36,817
Did you see how the newbies
got all dressed up for the shoot?

87
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,026
[scoffs] Pathetic.

88
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:41,989
All that preparation just to be
in a tiny corner of the background on TV.

89
00:05:42,072 --> 00:05:44,449
I feel really bad for them, though.

90
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:47,161
-Exactly.
-[chuckles]

91
00:05:47,244 --> 00:05:49,788
Uh, this is not working fast enough.

92
00:05:49,872 --> 00:05:50,998
Huh? What was that?

93
00:05:52,666 --> 00:05:54,418
[exhales sharply] Oh.

94
00:05:58,297 --> 00:06:00,465
[gasps] I shouldn't waste time here.

95
00:06:00,549 --> 00:06:02,342
I better go out and rehearse
with the cameras.

96
00:06:02,426 --> 00:06:03,635
[sighs, gasps]

97
00:06:07,055 --> 00:06:08,265
Oh…

98
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:16,023
I'm really sorry, E-den.

99
00:06:16,648 --> 00:06:17,858
Film him without knowing?

100
00:06:17,941 --> 00:06:19,067
[sighs]

101
00:06:19,151 --> 00:06:21,820
Don't put it that way. It sounds illegal.

102
00:06:22,404 --> 00:06:26,658
You'll just hit this button here
and turn the power on.

103
00:06:27,951 --> 00:06:30,621
And this thing
will automatically start filming him.

104
00:06:31,705 --> 00:06:32,706
I can't.

105
00:06:32,789 --> 00:06:35,292
I could never do that. [sighs]

106
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:37,127
I've gotta keep a low profile, okay?

107
00:06:37,211 --> 00:06:39,463
If I cause any more trouble,
I'll end up serving time.

108
00:06:39,546 --> 00:06:40,839
Mm-mmm. Mmm. Mmm. Mm-hmm.

109
00:06:40,923 --> 00:06:42,132
Come on, sit down. Sit down.

110
00:06:42,966 --> 00:06:45,594
-[sighs]
-Come on, I get how mean Ga Woo-su is,

111
00:06:45,677 --> 00:06:47,721
but he's not sending a student to jail.

112
00:06:47,804 --> 00:06:51,391
And you need to do this to make up
for messing around in my class.

113
00:06:52,017 --> 00:06:53,852
The nerve you had
to write that in my class.

114
00:06:53,936 --> 00:06:55,604
Do you even know how hurt I was?

115
00:06:55,687 --> 00:06:59,858
Th-That… [sighs]
I'm really sorry about that, but…

116
00:07:01,318 --> 00:07:05,239
Of all the students here,
do you not get why I'm doing this?

117
00:07:05,322 --> 00:07:06,573
Nope.

118
00:07:08,408 --> 00:07:09,826
Well, if you don't do it…

119
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,080
we'll all be fired.

120
00:07:13,163 --> 00:07:14,289
Do you get it?

121
00:07:14,373 --> 00:07:15,540
You're getting fired?

122
00:07:16,708 --> 00:07:19,169
This is a direct order from the principal.

123
00:07:19,962 --> 00:07:23,215
Do you know what happens
when someone goes against her will?

124
00:07:23,298 --> 00:07:24,967
We get fired.

125
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:27,302
And for me? "Not a problem."

126
00:07:27,386 --> 00:07:28,637
[inhales sharply]

127
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:29,721
But…

128
00:07:30,597 --> 00:07:34,559
it will be a problem for the PE
and Korean lit teachers.

129
00:07:36,603 --> 00:07:38,689
What about them?
What would happen to them?

130
00:07:39,564 --> 00:07:43,402
It won't be easy for Mr. Jung
to get hired given his leg issue.

131
00:07:44,611 --> 00:07:47,322
Oh, and Mr. Yoon… Yeah…

132
00:07:56,248 --> 00:07:57,249
Oh…

133
00:07:58,166 --> 00:07:59,459
That's not good at all.

134
00:07:59,543 --> 00:08:01,920
-That's right. It's not good.
-[sighs]

135
00:08:02,796 --> 00:08:04,214
And…

136
00:08:05,674 --> 00:08:06,925
I know everything, kid.

137
00:08:08,051 --> 00:08:10,220
-Know what?
-Come on, you know what.

138
00:08:10,929 --> 00:08:12,723
Do you have any idea how fast I caught on?

139
00:08:13,432 --> 00:08:15,183
I could tell right away. [scoffs]

140
00:08:15,267 --> 00:08:17,644
Did you actually think
you could hide it? [scoffs]

141
00:08:19,146 --> 00:08:22,065
Well, I don't quite follow. [chuckles]

142
00:08:23,817 --> 00:08:25,444
I knew about it all.

143
00:08:26,570 --> 00:08:27,696
From the beginning.

144
00:08:29,656 --> 00:08:31,533
Yeah, your rough thoughts

145
00:08:32,284 --> 00:08:33,452
and anxious looks.

146
00:08:33,535 --> 00:08:35,746
[scoffs] Mmm. I knew it all.

147
00:08:35,829 --> 00:08:37,205
[inhales sharply]

148
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,249
I won't say a word

149
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,043
if you do the filming.

150
00:08:41,126 --> 00:08:42,127
Okay?

151
00:08:48,675 --> 00:08:51,011
[sighs] How did he find out
I write novels?

152
00:08:53,347 --> 00:08:55,432
Girls, girls, girls.
What's all this chatter?

153
00:08:55,515 --> 00:08:58,185
You know what's going on.
We're shooting the TV show.

154
00:08:58,268 --> 00:09:00,812
[audio speeds up]

155
00:09:00,896 --> 00:09:03,398
You're the faces
of Murim Girls' High School.

156
00:09:04,024 --> 00:09:06,026
Come on, girls!

157
00:09:06,109 --> 00:09:07,944
I can't believe not even one of you is…

158
00:09:08,028 --> 00:09:09,571
[audio speeds up]

159
00:09:09,654 --> 00:09:11,365
All right, do one of your Spanish lessons.

160
00:09:11,448 --> 00:09:14,117
And you, solve some math problems.
Isn't that fun?

161
00:09:15,035 --> 00:09:16,036
Dear?

162
00:09:17,079 --> 00:09:18,080
Dear?

163
00:09:19,456 --> 00:09:20,707
Dear.

164
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:21,958
Ji-a.

165
00:09:22,542 --> 00:09:23,668
Ji-a.

166
00:09:24,503 --> 00:09:26,880
Thank you, Jenny.

167
00:09:27,672 --> 00:09:28,715
And your uniform?

168
00:09:30,384 --> 00:09:32,427
-It's in the wash.
-Why?

169
00:09:33,136 --> 00:09:34,513
Why did you have to wash it

170
00:09:34,596 --> 00:09:36,890
when you obviously knew
you had to come to school?

171
00:09:37,682 --> 00:09:38,892
I spilled oil on it.

172
00:09:41,103 --> 00:09:43,814
You should have worn it
even if you had oil on it.

173
00:09:43,897 --> 00:09:46,191
Or you should have just taken it out
from the washing machine

174
00:09:46,274 --> 00:09:47,692
and worn it even if it was still wet.

175
00:09:47,776 --> 00:09:49,778
Why today of all days?

176
00:09:49,861 --> 00:09:50,862
And your gym clothes?

177
00:09:50,946 --> 00:09:51,947
Don't have them.

178
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:54,783
Borrow them from someone else!

179
00:09:54,866 --> 00:09:56,034
Actually, no.

180
00:09:56,118 --> 00:09:58,036
No, that won't do. Hey, what's your name?

181
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,204
Choi Ji-a.

182
00:09:59,287 --> 00:10:00,330
Follow me with your desk.

183
00:10:01,289 --> 00:10:02,999
Move it. You're going slow.

184
00:10:03,083 --> 00:10:04,751
We don't have time.

185
00:10:07,254 --> 00:10:08,255
What's going on?

186
00:10:08,839 --> 00:10:09,840
Oh…

187
00:10:09,923 --> 00:10:12,342
Mr. Ga. Uh…

188
00:10:12,426 --> 00:10:16,805
Well, you see, I'm going to have her
study alone in the counseling room

189
00:10:16,888 --> 00:10:18,098
until the fifth period.

190
00:10:18,181 --> 00:10:20,183
-Come on, grab your desk.
-[Woo-su] Go back in.

191
00:10:22,269 --> 00:10:23,520
Mr. Ga.

192
00:10:23,603 --> 00:10:26,898
Could I have a word
with you, please? [chuckles]

193
00:10:29,651 --> 00:10:32,779
You know, EBC is coming here
to film their show today.

194
00:10:32,863 --> 00:10:35,740
This lazy girl dozes off
during class all the time

195
00:10:35,824 --> 00:10:37,200
and she's not wearing her uniform.

196
00:10:37,284 --> 00:10:40,579
I know that's her thing.

197
00:10:40,662 --> 00:10:41,705
[clicks tongue, inhales sharply]

198
00:10:41,788 --> 00:10:45,125
But if she's going to ruin
this school's reputation on our big day,

199
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,626
she's better off not here.

200
00:10:46,710 --> 00:10:50,380
I would freak out if they show her
on camera dressed like that.

201
00:10:51,006 --> 00:10:54,301
I don't think this TV show
is worth making a student invisible.

202
00:10:54,926 --> 00:10:58,305
Wow, you're kind of naive,
you know that, Mr. Ga?

203
00:10:58,388 --> 00:11:00,432
TV shows are all scripted anyway.

204
00:11:00,515 --> 00:11:02,142
Just until fifth period, okay?

205
00:11:02,225 --> 00:11:03,351
Dear.

206
00:11:03,435 --> 00:11:05,645
If you insist on removing her
from the show,

207
00:11:06,146 --> 00:11:09,399
I won't let any of my students
participate in the filming.

208
00:11:10,859 --> 00:11:12,027
[scoffs]

209
00:11:14,696 --> 00:11:15,989
Who are you to say that?

210
00:11:16,573 --> 00:11:17,991
[inhales sharply] Mr. Ga.

211
00:11:18,074 --> 00:11:20,785
I believe I've explained this enough
for you to understand by now.

212
00:11:22,287 --> 00:11:23,288
Come on.

213
00:11:23,914 --> 00:11:24,915
Move!

214
00:11:28,335 --> 00:11:29,419
[Young-hee sighs]

215
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,425
[Young-hee breathes shakily]

216
00:11:36,009 --> 00:11:39,763
[straining]

217
00:11:39,846 --> 00:11:41,056
Oh, no.

218
00:11:42,057 --> 00:11:43,058
[gasps]

219
00:11:43,725 --> 00:11:45,894
I'll talk to you later, Mr. Ga. [chuckles]

220
00:11:45,977 --> 00:11:49,189
Yes, hi. I'm coming. [chuckles]

221
00:11:50,148 --> 00:11:52,400
Back inside. Everyone sit down.

222
00:11:58,323 --> 00:12:00,492
[pop music playing]

223
00:12:00,575 --> 00:12:05,038
CHAPTER 24:
OUR SCHOOL RIGHT NOW

224
00:12:19,427 --> 00:12:20,804
Hi, I'm Jenny.

225
00:12:20,887 --> 00:12:24,808
And I'm on an exchange student program
in Murim Girls' High School.

226
00:12:24,891 --> 00:12:26,768
Oh, I'm also from Singapore.

227
00:12:27,978 --> 00:12:30,855
Um, why did you choose Murim Girls' High?

228
00:12:30,939 --> 00:12:32,023
Oh, okay.

229
00:12:32,107 --> 00:12:36,111
So Murim Girls' High School
is super famous in Singapore.

230
00:12:36,194 --> 00:12:39,030
Internationally too, it's known to be
like a really good school.

231
00:12:39,114 --> 00:12:40,907
[chuckles] Uh, brag about our school? Uh…

232
00:12:40,991 --> 00:12:44,828
Yeah. Yeah, we have…
We have a really nice schoolyard.

233
00:12:44,911 --> 00:12:49,583
And… And our teachers…
Our teachers are super, super handsome.

234
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:51,209
-Yep, that's for real.
-Mr. Yoon Dong-ju.

235
00:12:51,293 --> 00:12:52,711
There's a teacher named Jung Gi-jeon.

236
00:12:52,794 --> 00:12:55,547
-No. No. Mr. Yoon Dong-ju…
-Uh-uh, it's Mr. Jung.

237
00:12:56,631 --> 00:12:59,384
Mr. Noh, I can't do it. I really can't.

238
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:00,677
[hisses]

239
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:02,679
-Yes, you can do it. Yes.
-[sighs] No.

240
00:13:02,762 --> 00:13:04,431
Why do you even think
that you can't do it?

241
00:13:04,514 --> 00:13:06,141
Stop having such weak thoughts. Come on.

242
00:13:06,224 --> 00:13:08,852
You're a Murim girl
with endless potential, kid.

243
00:13:08,935 --> 00:13:10,145
-Yeah.
-What does that even have to…

244
00:13:10,228 --> 00:13:11,563
Oh. He's here. I'm leaving.

245
00:13:11,646 --> 00:13:13,315
And get the job done, okay?

246
00:13:16,192 --> 00:13:17,485
I'm watching you.

247
00:13:19,904 --> 00:13:22,282
[chuckles]

248
00:13:24,701 --> 00:13:25,869
Here's an easy one.

249
00:13:25,952 --> 00:13:29,539
From these conditions,
we can derive two distinct equations.

250
00:13:30,123 --> 00:13:32,042
-First, let's find the value of x…
-[sighs]

251
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:34,502
[Eui-ju] He'll kill me
if he discovers that I'm filming him

252
00:13:34,586 --> 00:13:36,671
…the equation of this tangent line,
we can use it…

253
00:13:36,755 --> 00:13:39,466
But then he's exposed the fact
that I write novels

254
00:13:39,549 --> 00:13:41,885
after acting like he'd keep it a secret.

255
00:13:41,968 --> 00:13:43,637
So let's just do it.

256
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:44,846
Mr. Ga.

257
00:13:47,349 --> 00:13:48,350
I…

258
00:13:48,892 --> 00:13:50,560
I have a question I'd like to ask.

259
00:13:53,188 --> 00:13:54,189
What is it?

260
00:13:57,317 --> 00:13:58,902
Uh…

261
00:13:58,985 --> 00:14:01,738
Uh… Mr. Ga,

262
00:14:01,821 --> 00:14:07,160
I heard you got faculty offers
from renowned overseas universities.

263
00:14:07,243 --> 00:14:09,287
Why did you decide to teach here then?

264
00:14:12,248 --> 00:14:13,625
Why are you asking this now?

265
00:14:16,086 --> 00:14:18,254
Because I've thought about it
since you got here.

266
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:21,883
It's surprising a genius like you
chose to teach students here

267
00:14:21,966 --> 00:14:26,805
so I'm wondering
if there's a story behind it.

268
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:33,395
I believe that's the type of question
you ask after class.

269
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:36,022
-Oh, come on.
-[groans]

270
00:14:36,106 --> 00:14:38,274
-We wanna hear the story too.
-[groans]

271
00:14:38,358 --> 00:14:39,943
-Yes, I'm curious too.
-If you tell us the story,

272
00:14:40,026 --> 00:14:41,027
we'll study very hard!

273
00:14:41,111 --> 00:14:42,570
[students chanting] Tell us now!

274
00:14:42,654 --> 00:14:43,822
Tell us now!

275
00:14:43,905 --> 00:14:45,240
Tell us now!

276
00:14:45,323 --> 00:14:48,493
-Tell us now! Tell us now!
-Quiet down.

277
00:14:50,161 --> 00:14:52,997
All right. This story may actually
be of help to you

278
00:14:53,081 --> 00:14:54,708
in deciding which career
to choose in life.

279
00:14:58,837 --> 00:14:59,838
For the Olympiad,

280
00:14:59,921 --> 00:15:04,426
they select six students that have to
go through two rounds of training camp.

281
00:15:04,509 --> 00:15:06,428
On the day we arrived,
for the first round,

282
00:15:06,511 --> 00:15:09,431
after checking in,
a test was already waiting for us.

283
00:15:10,014 --> 00:15:11,224
That test… [sighs]

284
00:15:40,336 --> 00:15:41,838
[gasps]

285
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:49,679
Take it out.

286
00:15:51,556 --> 00:15:52,766
Take it out now.

287
00:15:59,773 --> 00:16:00,982
[gasps]

288
00:16:05,236 --> 00:16:07,155
[student] Wow… [whispers indistinctly]

289
00:16:11,576 --> 00:16:13,453
Mr. Ga! Mr. Ga! Wait!

290
00:16:13,536 --> 00:16:16,581
The Japanese language teacher said
all the teachers would get fired

291
00:16:16,664 --> 00:16:19,459
if I didn't do it.
That's why I did it, Mr. Ga.

292
00:16:19,542 --> 00:16:21,753
Mr. Ga, please hear me out this once.

293
00:16:21,836 --> 00:16:24,130
I couldn't let
the teachers get fired, Mr. Ga.

294
00:16:24,214 --> 00:16:26,132
Please hear me out, Mr. Ga. I…

295
00:16:27,592 --> 00:16:31,179
Noh Da-ju, how could you use a student
to film me? Have you lost it?

296
00:16:35,308 --> 00:16:37,685
Mr. Ga Woo-su, can you please calm down

297
00:16:38,269 --> 00:16:39,312
so we can talk it out?

298
00:16:39,896 --> 00:16:42,065
Someone filmed you
behind your back? [chuckles]

299
00:16:42,148 --> 00:16:43,149
How could… [chuckles]

300
00:16:43,775 --> 00:16:45,693
…someone ever do that?

301
00:16:46,778 --> 00:16:48,780
Did you really have to shove a camera
in my face?

302
00:16:48,863 --> 00:16:50,907
-You of all people?
-Guys, guys. Stop.

303
00:16:50,990 --> 00:16:52,325
What's going on, huh?

304
00:16:52,408 --> 00:16:53,493
Hey.

305
00:16:53,576 --> 00:16:55,245
That was a long time ago.

306
00:16:55,328 --> 00:16:56,538
You've gotta get over it.

307
00:16:56,621 --> 00:16:58,039
You're still dwelling on that?

308
00:17:01,626 --> 00:17:03,878
Hey! Hey, hey, hey! Hey!

309
00:17:05,672 --> 00:17:07,215
[Young-hee] Mr. Ga Woo-su.

310
00:17:10,969 --> 00:17:12,679
Could I have a moment with you?

311
00:17:17,642 --> 00:17:18,643
[sighs]

312
00:17:19,394 --> 00:17:20,603
Woo-su.

313
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,565
[sighs]

314
00:17:26,484 --> 00:17:28,903
-[groans]
-You're unbelievable.

315
00:17:28,987 --> 00:17:31,698
-Mr. Jung… [stammers]
-[sighs] This is nuts.

316
00:17:31,781 --> 00:17:32,782
W-What is it?

317
00:17:32,866 --> 00:17:35,451
Did something happen
to Mr. Ga in the past?

318
00:17:35,535 --> 00:17:36,995
[sighs, clicks tongue]

319
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,126
I don't know the details.

320
00:17:44,252 --> 00:17:45,670
But when Woo-su was ten,

321
00:17:46,838 --> 00:17:49,799
after being on a TV show,
he ended up being stalked.

322
00:17:50,675 --> 00:17:52,093
That darn stalker

323
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,888
would go to his school
and even to his house.

324
00:17:54,971 --> 00:17:57,348
He filmed him without him knowing
what was going on.

325
00:17:57,432 --> 00:17:58,808
It was a total mess.

326
00:17:58,892 --> 00:17:59,934
Later on,

327
00:18:01,519 --> 00:18:02,896
he kidnapped Woo-su.

328
00:18:04,355 --> 00:18:05,398
Kidnapped him?

329
00:18:15,325 --> 00:18:16,910
[Gi-jeon] It traumatized him.

330
00:18:22,165 --> 00:18:23,458
[sighs]

331
00:18:25,710 --> 00:18:27,837
Oh… [sighs]

332
00:18:27,921 --> 00:18:29,422
[exhales sharply] Oh, dear. [whimpers]

333
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,508
-What's wrong?
-[whimpers]

334
00:18:33,593 --> 00:18:35,011
[Young-hee] Mr. Ga Woo-su.

335
00:18:35,094 --> 00:18:37,221
This is the real world.

336
00:18:37,305 --> 00:18:40,016
People who know how to listen
survive longer

337
00:18:40,099 --> 00:18:43,728
than those who think being smart
is enough to get by.

338
00:18:43,811 --> 00:18:46,648
It's not like your face is going
to wear out just because we're filming it.

339
00:18:46,731 --> 00:18:48,816
Stop making such a fuss.

340
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:51,069
-[inhales, sighs]
-[sighs]

341
00:18:52,487 --> 00:18:53,655
Please excuse me.

342
00:18:54,656 --> 00:18:56,783
If you're not willing to cooperate,

343
00:18:56,866 --> 00:18:59,327
you leave me with no choice.

344
00:19:06,876 --> 00:19:08,503
SUSPENSION NOTICE

345
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:10,713
YOON DONG-JU

346
00:19:10,797 --> 00:19:13,841
I'm sure the other teachers
must have other options as well.

347
00:19:14,634 --> 00:19:16,761
But it'll be quite tough
for Mr. Yoon Dong-ju

348
00:19:16,844 --> 00:19:18,429
if he gets fired, right?

349
00:19:26,354 --> 00:19:28,314
[Woo-su] Now, we can see that negative 4

350
00:19:28,398 --> 00:19:30,566
is the average rate of change
in this equation.

351
00:19:30,650 --> 00:19:32,777
Next, we need to find the f prime of x.

352
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:34,278
[chalk writing]

353
00:19:34,362 --> 00:19:35,738
Two x minus three.

354
00:19:35,822 --> 00:19:37,740
What's the average rate of change again?

355
00:19:37,824 --> 00:19:39,450
[students] Negative four.

356
00:19:40,827 --> 00:19:42,245
Yes, it's negative four.

357
00:19:46,374 --> 00:19:48,710
He could have just agreed
to the filming from the start.

358
00:19:48,793 --> 00:19:50,086
What was all that circus for?

359
00:19:51,212 --> 00:19:52,505
My point exactly.

360
00:19:52,588 --> 00:19:54,007
We're finishing late because of him.

361
00:19:54,090 --> 00:19:55,675
-[Woo-su] Therefore, the value of x is…
-What the heck is this?

362
00:19:55,758 --> 00:19:57,343
-So annoying.
-…is negative one-half.

363
00:19:57,427 --> 00:20:01,264
And negative one-half is a number
that falls between negative three and two.

364
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:06,686
Therefore… [sighs] …c is…

365
00:20:09,188 --> 00:20:10,565
[sighs]

366
00:20:11,315 --> 00:20:13,026
We're finally done with it all.

367
00:20:13,109 --> 00:20:15,278
CHAPTER 25: I ONLY FEEL BETRAYED
BECAUSE I TRUSTED YOU

368
00:20:17,572 --> 00:20:19,323
[chuckles]

369
00:20:19,824 --> 00:20:21,200
[snores]

370
00:20:21,284 --> 00:20:23,327
[yawns]

371
00:20:23,411 --> 00:20:25,496
[groaning]

372
00:20:28,041 --> 00:20:30,043
[gasps] Auntie!

373
00:20:30,626 --> 00:20:32,545
What… What am I doing here?

374
00:20:32,628 --> 00:20:34,922
You said you couldn't sleep
at all last night

375
00:20:35,006 --> 00:20:36,382
and wanted to get rest.

376
00:20:36,466 --> 00:20:38,634
Were you asleep all along?

377
00:20:38,718 --> 00:20:40,720
I… I was?

378
00:20:41,512 --> 00:20:42,513
That makes no sense.

379
00:20:43,222 --> 00:20:44,265
And the show?

380
00:20:44,348 --> 00:20:46,684
They're done filming it all.

381
00:20:46,768 --> 00:20:47,769
What?

382
00:20:48,311 --> 00:20:49,729
[exclaims] Oh, no.

383
00:20:49,812 --> 00:20:51,898
[exclaims] Oh, no!

384
00:20:53,691 --> 00:20:56,360
No. No. Don't go. No. Please.

385
00:20:56,444 --> 00:20:59,280
Auntie, they're leaving.
They're actually leaving.

386
00:20:59,363 --> 00:21:00,740
They're leaving!

387
00:21:00,823 --> 00:21:03,242
No!

388
00:21:03,326 --> 00:21:05,328
[flute playing]

389
00:21:32,814 --> 00:21:34,398
[sighs]

390
00:21:34,482 --> 00:21:36,567
Just stop that!

391
00:21:46,869 --> 00:21:47,954
[sighs]

392
00:21:49,997 --> 00:21:51,874
[whimpers]

393
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:53,417
[groans, sniffles]

394
00:21:54,043 --> 00:21:55,503
M-Mr. Ga.

395
00:21:58,339 --> 00:21:59,715
[breathes shakily]

396
00:21:59,799 --> 00:22:01,008
Mr. Ga.

397
00:22:13,604 --> 00:22:14,689
[breathes shakily]

398
00:22:27,493 --> 00:22:28,995
[breathes shakily] Well…

399
00:22:29,704 --> 00:22:31,080
Mr. Ga.

400
00:22:33,416 --> 00:22:35,293
Mr. Ga, I'm so sorry.

401
00:22:36,294 --> 00:22:39,922
I would have never taken a video of you
if I had known what you went through.

402
00:22:41,215 --> 00:22:42,216
I mean,

403
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:44,468
I shouldn't have done it regardless.
I'm so sorry.

404
00:22:44,552 --> 00:22:47,263
It's my fault. I'm very, very sorry.

405
00:22:52,727 --> 00:22:54,270
[exhales sharply]

406
00:22:54,353 --> 00:22:56,314
You asked me a question during class.

407
00:22:57,315 --> 00:22:59,901
Guess what crossed my mind
in that split second.

408
00:23:03,613 --> 00:23:05,406
"Is she finally interested in math?"

409
00:23:11,704 --> 00:23:13,664
After hearing your question, I thought,

410
00:23:14,916 --> 00:23:16,417
"She may start with something unrelated.

411
00:23:17,793 --> 00:23:20,046
Maybe she'll gain
a little bit of interest in math

412
00:23:20,129 --> 00:23:21,923
once she hears
what I've been through in life."

413
00:23:22,798 --> 00:23:25,051
So I tried to give you an earnest answer.

414
00:23:27,303 --> 00:23:28,304
But you…

415
00:23:32,975 --> 00:23:34,018
[sighs]

416
00:23:35,061 --> 00:23:36,729
I felt let down

417
00:23:36,812 --> 00:23:38,606
because I put my trust in you.

418
00:23:40,650 --> 00:23:42,068
Forget it. Go home.

419
00:23:47,490 --> 00:23:49,283
Sorry for letting you down.

420
00:23:49,909 --> 00:23:52,286
I'm really sorry. [breathes shakily]

421
00:23:52,370 --> 00:23:53,371
Go.

422
00:23:54,789 --> 00:23:56,582
[breathes shakily]

423
00:24:02,171 --> 00:24:04,006
[winces]

424
00:24:04,924 --> 00:24:06,259
[groans]

425
00:24:07,426 --> 00:24:08,886
[whimpers]

426
00:24:11,138 --> 00:24:12,139
Get up.

427
00:24:13,182 --> 00:24:14,809
Your act isn't going to work.

428
00:24:15,476 --> 00:24:17,019
[Eui-ju inhales sharply]

429
00:24:17,103 --> 00:24:18,187
[grunting]

430
00:24:18,271 --> 00:24:22,108
[wincing]

431
00:24:22,191 --> 00:24:23,276
Eui-ju.

432
00:24:25,152 --> 00:24:26,153
Eui-ju.

433
00:24:28,155 --> 00:24:30,157
Eui-ju. Eui-ju.

434
00:24:30,241 --> 00:24:31,701
Wake up, Eui-ju!

435
00:24:32,868 --> 00:24:34,203
Eui-ju.

436
00:24:34,287 --> 00:24:35,454
Wake up, Eui-ju!

437
00:24:35,538 --> 00:24:37,790
[Eui-ju breathing heavily]

438
00:24:39,792 --> 00:24:41,502
[whimpering]

439
00:24:42,253 --> 00:24:44,547
[somber music playing]
